data.title: Princess Alexandra of Denmark (later Queen Alexandra, wife of Edward VII) with her two eldest sons, Prince Albert Victor (Eddy) and George Frederick Ernest Albert (later George V)
data.meta_description:
Wow!  Just once in a while you're flicking through something very innocent looking, in this case a small album of anonymous cartes de visites, and then a little clue leads to a whole discovery.
	
	This is one of two CdVs I discovered (see neighbouring image) taken by Russell & Sons, Chichester.
	
	In this one we see a young (c. 32 year old, in 1876) Princess Alexandra, standing with two of her sons.  Alexandra married Albert Edward, Prince of Wales (later Edward VII) in 1863 at the age of just 18.  She quickly had a number of children, and by deduction I have determined that the elder one shown here is Prince Albert Victor (Eddy), and the younger one is George Frederick Ernest Albert, later to become George V.

She quickly had a number of children, and by deduction I have determined that the elder one shown here is Prince Albert Victor (Eddy), and the younger one is George Frederick Ernest Albert, later to become George V.
